PROMPT: View and customize your command prompt

Syntax: prompt
        prompt <string>
        prompt default
        prompt tokens

DESCRIPTION:
  By default your prompt automatically shows the stat pools that
  apply to your race and OCC. An MDC being with magic sees:
    MDC:450/450 PPE:120/120>
  while an SDC character with psionics sees:
    HP:80/80 SDC:200/200 ISP:60/60>
  Pools you do not have (no PPE, no ISP) are not shown.

  prompt            Show your current prompt setting.
  prompt <string>   Set a custom prompt. Tokens like $k (current MDC)
                    or $p (current PPE) are expanded each time the
                    prompt is displayed; see 'prompt tokens'.
  prompt default    Return to the automatic pool display.
                    ('prompt reset' does the same.)
  prompt tokens     List every available token.

  The words 'default', 'reset', and 'tokens' are reserved by this
  command. To set a prompt literally starting with one of them, use
  'set PROMPT <string>' instead.

EXAMPLE:
  prompt [$k/$K MDC $p/$P PPE]>
  prompt default

SEE ALSO: sbar, score, set, unset
